@@eThe Northern Corridor: A Ledger Perspective@@N

@@yRegistry of Joint Governance, Northern Division@@N
@@dFiled under: Trade Corridor Administration, Lantern Road Operations@@N

The Great Northern Forest is not wilderness to Midgaard. It is a
@@ymanaged trade corridor@@N -- four hundred square miles of negotiated
passage connecting our southern markets to @@yKowloon's@@N delta ports.
Every lantern post, every waystone, every ford marker along the
@@yLantern Road@@N exists because a clerk in the Joint Oversight Bureau
authorized its placement and a warden under the @@WOath of the Counted
Step@@N confirmed its position.

The @@WNorthern Covenant@@N remains one of Midgaard's finest diplomatic
achievements. Signed at the Oath-Crossing glade, it established joint
governance neither city could manage alone. Our @@eLedgerhouse@@N holds
the original -- @@dparchment eleven, northern drawer, third vault@@N.
The Continuity faction considers it proof that process produces peace.
The Reckoning faction notes the fourteen sealed amendments no citizen
has been permitted to read.

@@rThe Ash Winters nearly broke us.@@N Volcanic fallout from the
Cinderteeth poisoned streams and killed a third of the large game.
Patrol reports fill six volumes with logistics failures: spoiled
grain, collapsed bridges, convoy losses exceeding thirty percent. The
@@yPassage Tithe@@N -- payment in grain, salt, lamp oil, and iron nails
rather than coin -- was born from that crisis. Not generosity.
@@yAdministrative adaptation@@N.

Our wardens maintain the @@gSouthern Verge@@N with relay patrols and
quarterly audits. Beyond the @@dIronpine Rise@@N, governance becomes
shared. Beyond the @@eAncestor Deeps@@N, Kowloon's Wardens of Iron hold
primary jurisdiction. Handoff protocols fill three registry volumes.

@@gRoadwardens@@N answer to the Joint Bureau. @@dMire-clans@@N hold barter
licenses renewed each equinox. @@WStone-antler circles@@N receive ritual
access writs our clerks process but do not claim to understand.
@@rAshfang warbands@@N appear in our ledgers only as losses -- raided
convoys and the unsettling suspicion that someone in our own bureaus
sells route schedules.

The @@ylantern-and-scale@@N motif on waystones is Midgaard's signature:
light and measure. When patrol reports note a @@Wwhite stag@@N sighting,
the Bureau doubles escorts. When the @@rred moss bloom@@N appears,
quarantine advisories activate.

The forest proves governance can extend beyond walls. It also reminds
us that @@rgovernance is never finished@@N. Every season the canopy tests
another waystone. Every winter the road bends farther from where the
last survey placed it.
